<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="53" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1113,1288]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1113,1138]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Postgena and antepronotal setae as strong as dorsal thoracic setae. Cell dm somewhat truncate. M 
<number box="[1381,1389,1129,1143]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" value="1.0">1</number>
, M 
<number box="[1428,1436,1129,1143]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
and A 
<number box="[222,230,1167,1181]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" value="1.0">1</number>
veins rather evanescent distally. Hypandrium somewhat narrow at apex, subequal in diameter along its length. Female sternite 
<number box="[414,428,1191,1215]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" value="8.0">8</number>
elongate, thin distally.
</paragraph>
